                            <comment id="12863030" author="curtisr7" created="Sat, 1 May 2010 18:01:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;One thing I want to point out is that JPAFacadeHelper.toOpenJPAObjectId(..) will now throw a RuntimeException. This could cause a behavior change for any users currently using the java.persistence.Cache interface improperly. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, if they call javax.persistence.Cache.evict(Class, oid) and oid isn&apos;t a valid oid for the provided Class, we will now throw a UserException. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12863032" author="curtisr7" created="Sat, 1 May 2010 18:02:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Comitted rev 940077 to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
